<p>The penalties are harsh because they&#8217;re meant to be a deterrent. Unfortunately, deterrents don&#8217;t work if nobody knows about them. Many people don&#8217;t realize that a second DUI conviction in Ontario results in MANDATORY jail time &#8211; the judge cannot waive it. As of 2011, the minimum is 30 days, up from two weeks. I talked to a lawyer who SPECIALIZES in DUI cases, who was not aware of this most recent penalty increase.</p>
